record_data.record_plain_text: BUCKEYE POWER, INC. RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 3 REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE BUCKEYE POWER, INC. RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 3 REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE - ROBERT P. MONE GENERATING PLANT Buckeye Power, Inc. ("Buckeye") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Robert P. Mone Generating Plant ("Mone Plant") in Van Wert County, Ohio to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule FERC No. 3 sets forth Buckeye's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Mone Plant to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation or other source owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Supply Service. Buckeye's revenue requirement for the Mone Plant consists of the sum of the charges for the Fixed Capability Component and the Heating Losses Component. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This rate schedule shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. ANNUAL AND MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENTS: 1. FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $1,195,756.56. The monthly charge to PJM is $99,646.38. 2. HEATING LOSSES COMPONENT The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Losses Component is $0. The monthly charge to PJM is $0.00. In summary, the total annual revenue requirement is $1,195,756.56. The total monthly revenue requirement is $99,646.38.
